<p>Weather patterns in Arkansas generally favor solar production, with the majority of precipitation occurring during winter months when solar output is naturally lower. Summer months typically see clear skies and intense sunshine, maximizing solar panel efficiency when electricity demand peaks. Modern solar panels maintain excellent performance even in Arkansas's occasionally high temperatures, with quality systems including temperature coefficients that minimize efficiency losses during the hottest days of summer.</p>

